Sec. 63.153. SECURITY REQUIREMENTS. A person who engages in
the sale of ammonium nitrate or ammonium nitrate material shall take
steps to secure the ammonium nitrate or ammonium nitrate material
stored at the person's facility against vandalism, theft, or other
unauthorized access, including:
(1) ensuring that a storage facility is fenced or otherwise
enclosed and locked when unattended;
(2) inspecting a storage facility daily for signs of
vandalism and to verify its structural integrity; and
(3) establishing and maintaining ongoing inventory control
procedures for the ammonium nitrate or ammonium nitrate material.
Added by Acts 2007, 80th Leg., R.S., Ch. 483 (H.B. 2546), Sec. 1, eff.
September 1, 2007.

